gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Magic 122, Nuggets 120
gameRecap.excerpt: The Magic outscored the Nuggets, 68-53 in the second half, as they snap a 3-game losing streak and defeat Denver 122-120. Paolo Banchero tallied the first triple-double of his career with 32 points, 10 rebounds, and 11 assists as Jalen Suggs had a career-high 27 points and seven 3PT FG. Cole Anthony tallied 23 points for Orlando as well. Nikola Jokic led Denver with 29 points (13-19 FG), four rebounds, and eight assists while Jamal Murray added 20 points, seven rebounds, and nine assists. The Magic move to 20-15 while the Nuggets move to 25-12.
